    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="74"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">753.94/9–1144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-11T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 11, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2489. According to general instructions issued by the Chiefs of Staff to the
                    British and American delegations for forthcoming staff conversations, these
                    conversations will be concerned entirely with Portuguese participation in
                    eventual Timor expedition. The scope of the conversations will not include other
                    Portuguese possessions such as Macao, or Allied facilities in the Azores or
                    other Portuguese territory.</p>
                <p>The mission will be under the general guidance of the British and American
                    Ambassadors, but it is understood that the delegations will be free to refer to
                    the Chiefs of Staff at any time for guidance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
